    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>204. National Security Action Memorandum No. 303<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d204fn1">Source: National Archives and Records Administration, RG
                        59, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                        Files: Lot 70 D 265, General. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-06-02">June 2, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Change in Name of Special Group 5412</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Henceforth, the Special Group 5412 will be known as the 303
                            Committee.<note n="2" xml:id="d204fn2">An undated list identifies the
                            members of the 303 Committee as the President’s Special Assistant for
                            National Security Affairs <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">McGeorge
                                Bundy</persName>, Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                                corresp="#p_MCJA1">McCone</persName>, Acting Deputy Under Secretary
                            of State for Political Affairs <persName corresp="#p_TLET1"
                                >Thompson</persName>, and Deputy Secretary of Defense Vance.
                            (Ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>This change in no way alters the composition, function or responsibility
                        of the Special Group 5412 as authorized by <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5412/2, dated December 28, 1955.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d204fn3">See <ref target="#d257fn2">footnote 2, Document
                                257</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
